HEADWORD: Rhabdopleura
<hw>Rhab`do*pleu"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"ra`bdos</grk> a rod + <?/<?/<?/<?/ the side.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of marine Bryozoa in which the tubular
cells have a centralchitinous axis and the tentacles are borne on a
bilobed lophophore. It is the type of the order Pterobranchia, or
Podostomata</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

